sp.p:
To hear meekly, sir, and to laugh
moderately;
or to forbear both.

Pray you, do my commendations;
I
would be glad to see it.

Let me hear a staff, a stanze, a verse;
lege,
domine.

The third of the five vowels, if you
repeat them;
or the fifth, if I.

Offered by a child to an old man;
which is
wit-old.

Gentlemen and soldiers, pardon me;
I will
not combat in my shirt.

The naked truth of it is, I have no
shirt;
I go woolward for penance.

Welcome, Mercade;
But that thou interrupt'st
our merriment.
